<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Enow" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Enow,</orth> adj. sufficient, used as the plural of <emph>enough</emph>: <cit><quote>we were Christians e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.5.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 5, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his losses, e. to press a royal merchant down,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 29</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we have French quarrels e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.240" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 240</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.28" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.5.19" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.4.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 4, 11</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>